{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_016CsqmJ4zTJ4f8cg4E6Zw2D","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# OptionalInformer / API Discovery\n2\t\n3\tSource: `pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go`\n4\t\n5\t## Purpose\n6\t\n7\tThe cert-manager operator targets both full OpenShift clusters and stripped-down variants\n8\t(e.g., MicroShift) that do not serve every OpenShift API. `OptionalInformer` allows the\n9\toperator to start an informer factory for a given API group only when that API is actually\n10\tpresent on the cluster, with no special-casing scattered through startup code.\n11\t\n12\t## Core types\n13\t\n14\t### ResourceDiscoverer interface\n15\t\n16\t```go\n17\ttype ResourceDiscoverer interface {\n18\t    Discover() (bool, error)\n19\t}\n20\t```\n21\t\n22\tThe only implementation is `apiResourceDiscoverer`, constructed by `NewResourceDiscoverer`.\n23\tConstruction is cheap: no API call is made until `Discover()` is invoked. `Discover()` calls\n24\t`discovery.DiscoveryInterface.ServerResourcesForGroupVersion` for the GVR's group/version,\n25\tthen scans the returned resource list for the resource name.\n26\t\n27\t### OptionalInformer[T]\n28\t\n29\t```go\n30\ttype OptionalInformer[GroupInformer any] struct {\n31\t    InformerFactory *GroupInformer\n32\t}\n33\t```\n34\t\n35\tA typed wrapper that holds a pointer to an informer factory, or nil if the API was absent.\n36\tThe type parameter `T` is the concrete group informer factory type (e.g.,\n37\t`configinformers.SharedInformerFactory`).\n38\t\n39\t### InitInformerIfAvailable[T]\n40\t\n41\t```go\n42\tfunc InitInformerIfAvailable[groupInformer any](\n43\t    d ResourceDiscoverer,\n44\t    informerInitFunc func() groupInformer,\n45\t) (*OptionalInformer[groupInformer], error)\n46\t```\n47\t\n48\tThis is the entry point for callers. It:\n49\t1. Calls `d.Discover()`.\n50\t2. If discovery returns an error **other than NotFound**, propagates it — the operator cannot\n51\t   start safely without knowing whether the API is present.\n52\t3. If the API is **not found** (Discover returns false, nil), returns an `OptionalInformer`\n53\t   with `InformerFactory == nil`. No informer is started. The operator continues normally.\n54\t4. If the API is **found**, calls `informerInitFunc()`, stores the result in\n55\t   `InformerFactory`, and returns it.\n56\t\n57\tDiscovery NotFound errors are silently treated as absent — this covers MicroShift or any\n58\tcluster that simply hasn't installed a given API group.\n59\t\n60\t### Applicable() guard\n61\t\n62\t```go\n63\tfunc (o *OptionalInformer[GroupInformer]) Applicable() bool {\n64\t    return o.InformerFactory != nil\n65\t}\n66\t```\n67\t\n68\tCallers check `Applicable()` before accessing the factory. If false, the feature that\n69\tdepends on the optional API is silently skipped for the lifetime of the operator process\n70\t(there is no periodic re-check; the operator must restart to pick up a newly installed API).\n71\t\n72\t## Currently optional APIs\n73\t\n74\t| API | GVR | Used by |\n75\t|---|---|---|\n76\t| OpenShift Infrastructure | `config.openshift.io/v1 / infrastructures` | certmanager controller; passes proxy/infra topology to Deployment controllers |\n77\t| OpenShift FeatureGate | `config.openshift.io/v1 / featuregates` | `pkg/features`; gates preview features (e.g., TrustManager, IstioCSR) |\n78\t\n79\tThe FeatureGate case uses `ResourceDiscoverer` directly (calling `Discover()` and branching\n80\tmanually) rather than wrapping in `OptionalInformer`, because it only needs a one-time read\n81\trather than a live-watching informer factory.\n82\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20d91e02-72c5-45a5-97e1-59adfca2ee70","uuid":"f421d0f8-6dbb-430c-9113-6d7da5caa733","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:58:35.682Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-treatment/agentic/design-docs/components/optional-informer.md","content":"# OptionalInformer / API Discovery\n\nSource: `pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go`\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe cert-manager operator targets both full OpenShift clusters and stripped-down variants\n(e.g., MicroShift) that do not serve every OpenShift API. `OptionalInformer` allows the\noperator to start an informer factory for a given API group only when that API is actually\npresent on the cluster, with no special-casing scattered through startup code.\n\n## Core types\n\n### ResourceDiscoverer interface\n\n```go\ntype ResourceDiscoverer interface {\n    Discover() (bool, error)\n}\n```\n\nThe only implementation is `apiResourceDiscoverer`, constructed by `NewResourceDiscoverer`.\nConstruction is cheap: no API call is made until `Discover()` is invoked. `Discover()` calls\n`discovery.DiscoveryInterface.ServerResourcesForGroupVersion` for the GVR's group/version,\nthen scans the returned resource list for the resource name.\n\n### OptionalInformer[T]\n\n```go\ntype OptionalInformer[GroupInformer any] struct {\n    InformerFactory *GroupInformer\n}\n```\n\nA typed wrapper that holds a pointer to an informer factory, or nil if the API was absent.\nThe type parameter `T` is the concrete group informer factory type (e.g.,\n`configinformers.SharedInformerFactory`).\n\n### InitInformerIfAvailable[T]\n\n```go\nfunc InitInformerIfAvailable[groupInformer any](\n    d ResourceDiscoverer,\n    informerInitFunc func() groupInformer,\n) (*OptionalInformer[groupInformer], error)\n```\n\nThis is the entry point for callers. It:\n1. Calls `d.Discover()`.\n2. If discovery returns an error **other than NotFound**, propagates it — the operator cannot\n   start safely without knowing whether the API is present.\n3. If the API is **not found** (Discover returns false, nil), returns an `OptionalInformer`\n   with `InformerFactory == nil`. No informer is started. The operator continues normally.\n4. If the API is **found**, calls `informerInitFunc()`, stores the result in\n   `InformerFactory`, and returns it.\n\nDiscovery NotFound errors are silently treated as absent — this covers MicroShift or any\ncluster that simply hasn't installed a given API group.\n\n### Applicable() guard\n\n```go\nfunc (o *OptionalInformer[GroupInformer]) Applicable() bool {\n    return o.InformerFactory != nil\n}\n```\n\nCallers check `Applicable()` before accessing the factory. If false, the feature that\ndepends on the optional API is silently skipped for the lifetime of the operator process\n(there is no periodic re-check; the operator must restart to pick up a newly installed API).\n\n## Currently optional APIs\n\n| API | GVR | Used by |\n|---|---|---|\n| OpenShift Infrastructure | `config.openshift.io/v1 / infrastructures` | certmanager controller; passes proxy/infra topology to Deployment controllers |\n| OpenShift FeatureGate | `config.openshift.io/v1 / featuregates` | `pkg/features`; gates preview features (e.g., TrustManager, IstioCSR) |\n\nThe FeatureGate case uses `ResourceDiscoverer` directly (calling `Discover()` and branching\nmanually) rather than wrapping in `OptionalInformer`, because it only needs a one-time read\nrather than a live-watching informer factory.\n","numLines":82,"startLine":1,"totalLines":82}}}
