{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01CxBWk2Myq3KjsEdyw8ZPWL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete picture of the codebase. Here is the full implementation.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Implementation\n\n### File 1: `pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go`\n\nAdd `NewProxyInformerIfAvailable` at the end of the file:\n\n```go\n// pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go — full file with additions\n\npackage utils\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/discovery\"\n\n\tconfigv1 \"github.com/openshift/api/config/v1\"\n\tconfigv1client \"github.com/openshift/client-go/config/clientset/versioned\"\n\tconfiginformers \"github.com/openshift/client-go/config/informers/externalversions\"\n)\n\n// --- existing code unchanged through line 91 ---\n\n// NewProxyInformerIfAvailable discovers config.openshift.io/v1 Proxy and, when\n// the resource is served, returns an OptionalInformer whose factory can list\n// Proxy objects. On clusters that do not serve the Proxy API (MicroShift,\n// vanilla Kubernetes) the returned OptionalInformer has Applicable() == false.\nfunc NewProxyInformerIfAvailable(\n\tconfigClient configv1client.Interface,\n\tresyncInterval time.Duration,\n) (*OptionalInformer[configinformers.SharedInformerFactory], error) {\n\tproxyGVR := configv1.GroupVersion.WithResource(\"proxies\")\n\treturn InitInformerIfAvailable(\n\t\tNewResourceDiscoverer(proxyGVR, configClient.Discovery()),\n\t\tfunc() configinformers.SharedInformerFactory {\n\t\t\treturn configinformers.NewSharedInformerFactory(configClient, resyncInterval)\n\t\t},\n\t)\n}\n```\n\n**Exact diff** — add these imports and the function. The changes to the import block:\n\n```diff\n import (\n \t\"fmt\"\n+\t\"time\"\n \n \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n \t\"k8s.io/client-go/discovery\"\n+\n+\tconfigv1 \"github.com/openshift/api/config/v1\"\n+\tconfigv1client \"github.com/openshift/client-go/config/clientset/versioned\"\n+\tconfiginformers \"github.com/openshift/client-go/config/informers/externalversions\"\n )\n```\n\nAppend after the `Applicable()` method (line 91):\n\n```diff\n+\n+// NewProxyInformerIfAvailable discovers config.openshift.io/v1 Proxy and, when\n+// the resource is served, returns an OptionalInformer whose factory can list\n+// Proxy objects. On clusters that do not serve the Proxy API (MicroShift,\n+// vanilla Kubernetes) the returned OptionalInformer has Applicable() == false.\n+func NewProxyInformerIfAvailable(\n+\tconfigClient configv1client.Interface,\n+\tresyncInterval time.Duration,\n+) (*OptionalInformer[configinformers.SharedInformerFactory], error) {\n+\tproxyGVR := configv1.GroupVersion.WithResource(\"proxies\")\n+\treturn InitInformerIfAvailable(\n+\t\tNewResourceDiscoverer(proxyGVR, configClient.Discovery()),\n+\t\tfunc() configinformers.SharedInformerFactory {\n+\t\t\treturn configinformers.NewSharedInformerFactory(configClient, resyncInterval)\n+\t\t},\n+\t)\n+}\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 2: `pkg/operator/starter.go`\n\nThree changes: (a) create the proxy informer after the infra informer, (b) start it, (c) pass it into `ControllerConfig`.\n\n```diff\n--- a/pkg/operator/starter.go\n+++ b/pkg/operator/starter.go\n@@ -97,6 +97,12 @@ func RunOperator(ctx context.Context, cc *controllercmd.ControllerContext) error\n \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to discover Infrastructure presence: %w\", err)\n \t}\n \n+\toptProxyInformer, err := utils.NewProxyInformerIfAvailable(configClient, resyncInterval)\n+\tif err != nil {\n+\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to discover Proxy presence: %w\", err)\n+\t}\n+\n \tcertManagerControllerSet := certmanager.NewCertManagerControllerSet(\n \t\tkubeClient,\n \t\tkubeInformersForNamespaces,\n@@ -133,6 +139,10 @@ func RunOperator(ctx context.Context, cc *controllercmd.ControllerContext) error\n \t\t(*optInfraInformer.InformerFactory).Start(ctx.Done())\n \t}\n \n+\tif optProxyInformer.Applicable() {\n+\t\t(*optProxyInformer.InformerFactory).Start(ctx.Done())\n+\t}\n+\n \tfor _, controller := range controllersToStart {\n \t\tgo controller.Run(ctx, 1)\n \t}\n@@ -148,6 +158,7 @@ func RunOperator(ctx context.Context, cc *controllercmd.ControllerContext) error\n \t\tmanager, err := NewControllerManager(ControllerConfig{\n \t\t\tEnableIstioCSR:     istioCSREnabled,\n \t\t\tEnableTrustManager: trustManagerEnabled,\n+\t\t\tProxyInformer:      *optProxyInformer,\n \t\t})\n \t\tif err != nil {\n \t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create unified controller manager: %w\", err)\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 3: `pkg/operator/setup_manager.go`\n\nThree changes: (a) add proxy informer to `ControllerConfig`, (b) pass it to `setupTrustManagerController`, (c) update `setupTrustManagerController` to thread it through.\n\n```diff\n--- a/pkg/operator/setup_manager.go\n+++ b/pkg/operator/setup_manager.go\n@@ -21,12 +21,14 @@ import (\n \n \tcertmanagerv1 \"github.com/cert-manager/cert-manager/pkg/apis/certmanager/v1\"\n \n \tconfigv1 \"github.com/openshift/api/config/v1\"\n+\tconfiginformers \"github.com/openshift/client-go/config/informers/externalversions\"\n \tv1alpha1 \"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/api/operator/v1alpha1\"\n \t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n \t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/istiocsr\"\n \t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/trustmanager\"\n+\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/operator/utils\"\n \t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/version\"\n )\n \n@@ -114,8 +116,9 @@ var trustManagerManagedResources = []client.Object{\n // ControllerConfig specifies which controllers to enable in the unified manager.\n type ControllerConfig struct {\n \tEnableIstioCSR     bool\n \tEnableTrustManager bool\n+\tProxyInformer      utils.OptionalInformer[configinformers.SharedInformerFactory]\n }\n \n // NewControllerManager creates a unified manager for all enabled operand controllers.\n@@ -145,7 +148,7 @@ func NewControllerManager(config ControllerConfig) (*Manager, error) {\n \t}\n \n \tif config.EnableTrustManager {\n-\t\tif err := setupTrustManagerController(mgr); err != nil {\n+\t\tif err := setupTrustManagerController(mgr, config.ProxyInformer); err != nil {\n \t\t\treturn nil, err\n \t\t}\n \t}\n@@ -168,9 +171,9 @@ func setupIstioCSRController(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n }\n \n // setupTrustManagerController creates and registers the TrustManager controller with the manager.\n-func setupTrustManagerController(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n+func setupTrustManagerController(mgr ctrl.Manager, proxyInformer utils.OptionalInformer[configinformers.SharedInformerFactory]) error {\n \tsetupLog.Info(\"setting up controller\", \"name\", trustmanager.ControllerName)\n-\tr, err := trustmanager.New(mgr)\n+\tr, err := trustmanager.New(mgr, proxyInformer)\n \tif err != nil {\n \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create %s reconciler object: %w\", trustmanager.ControllerName, err)\n \t}\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 4: `pkg/controller/trustmanager/controller.go`\n\nTwo changes: (a) add `proxyInformer` to the `Reconciler` struct, (b) accept it in `New()`.\n\n```diff\n--- a/pkg/controller/trustmanager/controller.go\n+++ b/pkg/controller/trustmanager/controller.go\n@@ -18,6 +18,8 @@ import (\n \n \t\"github.com/go-logr/logr\"\n \n+\tconfiginformers \"github.com/openshift/client-go/config/informers/externalversions\"\n+\n \tcertmanagerv1 \"github.com/cert-manager/cert-manager/pkg/apis/certmanager/v1\"\n \n \tv1alpha1 \"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/api/operator/v1alpha1\"\n \t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n+\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/operator/utils\"\n )\n \n // RequestEnqueueLabelValue is the label value used for filtering reconcile\n@@ -38,6 +42,7 @@ type Reconciler struct {\n \teventRecorder record.EventRecorder\n \tlog           logr.Logger\n \tscheme        *runtime.Scheme\n+\tproxyInformer utils.OptionalInformer[configinformers.SharedInformerFactory]\n }\n \n // +kubebuilder:rbac:groups=operator.openshift.io,resources=trustmanagers,verbs=get;list;watch;update;patch\n@@ -60,13 +65,14 @@ type Reconciler struct {\n // +kubebuilder:rbac:groups=trust.cert-manager.io,resources=bundles/status,verbs=patch\n \n // New returns a new Reconciler instance.\n-func New(mgr ctrl.Manager) (*Reconciler, error) {\n+func New(mgr ctrl.Manager, proxyInformer utils.OptionalInformer[configinformers.SharedInformerFactory]) (*Reconciler, error) {\n \tc, err := common.NewClient(mgr)\n \tif err != nil {\n \t\treturn nil, err\n \t}\n \treturn &Reconciler{\n \t\tCtrlClient:    c,\n \t\tctx:           context.Background(),\n \t\teventRecorder: mgr.GetEventRecorderFor(ControllerName),\n \t\tlog:           ctrl.Log.WithName(ControllerName),\n \t\tscheme:        mgr.GetScheme(),\n+\t\tproxyInformer: proxyInformer,\n \t}, nil\n }\n```\n\nAlso add this RBAC marker after the existing ones (around line 59):\n\n```diff\n // +kubebuilder:rbac:groups=trust.cert-manager.io,resources=bundles/status,verbs=patch\n+// +kubebuilder:rbac:groups=config.openshift.io,resources=proxies,verbs=get;list;watch\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 5: `pkg/controller/trustmanager/deployments.go`\n\nTwo changes: (a) add `updateProxyEnv` method, (b) call it from `getDeploymentObject`.\n\n```diff\n--- a/pkg/controller/trustmanager/deployments.go\n+++ b/pkg/controller/trustmanager/deployments.go\n@@ -83,6 +83,10 @@ func (r *Reconciler) getDeploymentObject(trustManager *v1alpha1.TrustManager, re\n \tif err := updateNodeSelector(deployment, trustManager); err != nil {\n \t\treturn nil, err\n \t}\n+\n+\tif err := r.updateProxyEnv(deployment); err != nil {\n+\t\treturn nil, err\n+\t}\n \n \treturn deployment, nil\n }\n```\n\nAppend the new function at the end of the file (after `deploymentModified` and friends):\n\n```go\n// updateProxyEnv injects HTTP_PROXY, HTTPS_PROXY, and NO_PROXY environment\n// variables into the trust-manager container when the cluster Proxy API is\n// available. Values are read from the config.openshift.io/v1 Proxy/cluster\n// status, which contains the effective proxy settings computed by the cluster\n// network operator. On clusters without the Proxy API (MicroShift, vanilla\n// Kubernetes), this is a no-op.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) updateProxyEnv(deployment *appsv1.Deployment) error {\n\tif !r.proxyInformer.Applicable() {\n\t\treturn nil\n\t}\n\n\tproxyConfig, err := (*r.proxyInformer.InformerFactory).Config().V1().Proxies().Lister().Get(\"cluster\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.V(2).Info(\"unable to read cluster proxy settings, skipping proxy env injection\", \"error\", err)\n\t\treturn nil\n\t}\n\n\tvar proxyEnvVars []corev1.EnvVar\n\tif proxyConfig.Status.HTTPProxy != \"\" {\n\t\tproxyEnvVars = append(proxyEnvVars, corev1.EnvVar{Name: \"HTTP_PROXY\", Value: proxyConfig.Status.HTTPProxy})\n\t}\n\tif proxyConfig.Status.HTTPSProxy != \"\" {\n\t\tproxyEnvVars = append(proxyEnvVars, corev1.EnvVar{Name: \"HTTPS_PROXY\", Value: proxyConfig.Status.HTTPSProxy})\n\t}\n\tif proxyConfig.Status.NoProxy != \"\" {\n\t\tproxyEnvVars = append(proxyEnvVars, corev1.EnvVar{Name: \"NO_PROXY\", Value: proxyConfig.Status.NoProxy})\n\t}\n\n\tif len(proxyEnvVars) == 0 {\n\t\treturn nil\n\t}\n\n\tfor i, container := range deployment.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers {\n\t\tif container.Name == trustManagerContainerName {\n\t\t\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers[i].Env = append(\n\t\t\t\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers[i].Env,\n\t\t\t\tproxyEnvVars...,\n\t\t\t)\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of all changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go` | Add `NewProxyInformerIfAvailable` convenience function + OpenShift imports |\n| `pkg/operator/starter.go` | Create proxy informer, start its factory, pass via `ControllerConfig` |\n| `pkg/operator/setup_manager.go` | Add `ProxyInformer` to `ControllerConfig`, thread to `setupTrustManagerController` → `trustmanager.New` |\n| `pkg/controller/trustmanager/controller.go` | Add `proxyInformer` field to `Reconciler`, accept in `New()`, add RBAC marker |\n| `pkg/controller/trustmanager/deployments.go` | Add `updateProxyEnv` method, call from `getDeploymentObject` |\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# 1. Regenerate CRD manifests and deepcopy (picks up the new RBAC marker)\nmake update\n\n# 2. Verify vendor dependencies are consistent (no new deps needed —\n#    configv1, configv1client, configinformers are already vendored)\ngo build ./...\n\n# 3. Run unit tests\nmake test\n```\n\nNo new Go module dependencies are required — `github.com/openshift/api/config/v1`, `github.com/openshift/client-go/config/clientset/versioned`, and `github.com/openshift/client-go/config/informers/externalversions` are already vendored and used by `pkg/operator/starter.go` and `pkg/controller/certmanager/`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1730,"cache_read_input_tokens":73255,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1730,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20d91e02-72c5-45a5-97e1-59adfca2ee70","uuid":"d87f2a32-555a-4a1e-9435-84b8bb1939e7","timestamp":"2026-07-20T18:04:02.040Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDkDa7dmWN4ddFW7HmRF"}
